works.description: The works by American artist Jeff Koons are always the highlight of the auctions. Now, Jeff Koons’ iconic Pink Panther sculpture has fetched $16.8 million at Sotheby’s May 10 contemporary art auction. It was earlier expected to sell for between $20 million and $30 million. The 1988 porcelain sculpture of a semi-naked blonde woman hugging a pink panther toy is an edition of only three.
